1 Million YouTube Subscribers for Animal Watch! Thankyou so so much!!! It’s been a bucket list dream and now it’s a reality. This channel not only gave me the opportunities that terrestrial TV did not provide, it allowed me a way of escaping a very horrible and controlling marriage. It’s been tough, that’s not a joke! It’s been incredibly difficult and at times heart breaking but it allowed me the opportunity to prove myself and hopefully inspire others to use the internet and be an entrepreneur rather than a slave to others. I’ve swam with sharks, alligators, met the last two northern white rhinos, wolf packs, leopards and filmed the worlds most powerful dogs.…Thankyou to Ellen Hope Cobb, my ever devoted and brilliant cameralady and editor for her support over the years. Oh and a big 🖕 to all the twats who didn’t believe I could do it. Big hugs and love, Anneka xx ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️
.
.

Before and After 🔥🖤 @my_blue_wolf_ 💙🐺
Ocean is now getting more Wolfie traits that she’s over 1 year which includes more scent rolling, more vocalisation if she doesn’t like something, a little more cushion destruction (lol we are lucky that it’s just this) and trying to stalk and pounce on other dogs (it’s playful but different body language to your average Labrador so it freaks other dogs out) She is on the positive side though very submissive, very loving and super needy. Don’t let 30% wolf trick you as even that amount creates a LOT of additional wolf behaviour that dogs just don’t have. I’ve always had challenging dogs so I don’t notice it but other people would say that wolfdogs are too much work, so just don’t get one unless you have a work at home lifestyle and can put a tonne of socialisation and work into them. This is why I don’t promote puppies ever! I’m just too protective of these beautiful dogs. 💙
